        "title": "fix(claude-cli): return updatedInput in canUseTool allow response for Claude Code >= 2.1",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nClaude Code 2.1.x tightened the `PermissionResult` schema. The new union accepts:\n- `{ updatedInput: <record> }` — allow (with possibly-modified inputs)\n- `{ behavior: \"deny\", message: <string> }` — deny with reason\n\nOpenClaw's `canUseTool` adapter returned the deprecated `{ behavior: \"allow\" }` shape, which validated against neither branch and caused a `ZodError` before any tool could run.\n\nFixes #95171\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n**Behavior addressed**: `canUseTool` returns `{updatedInput: <record>}` instead of deprecated `{behavior: \"allow\"}` to match Claude Code >= 2.1's `PermissionResult` schema.\n\n**Real setup tested**: Node v24.13.1, Linux x86_64, worktree branch on openclaw/openclaw@main (e27c9a9a41)\n\n**Exact steps or command run after this patch**:\n\n```bash\nnode scripts/test-projects.mjs src/agents/harness/native-hook-relay.test.ts\n```\n\n**After-fix evidence**:\n\nTerminal capture of the actual test run:\n\n```\n> node scripts/test-projects.mjs \"src/agents/harness/native-hook-relay.test.ts\"\n\n RUN  v4.1.8\n\n Test Files  1 passed (1)\n      Tests  75 passed (75)\n   Start at  10:07:43\n   Duration  9.71s\n```\n\n**Observed result after the fix**: All 75 tests pass. The `renderPermissionDecisionResponse` adapter now:\n1. Accepts an optional `input` parameter for the permission request\n2. Returns `{ updatedInput: input }` for \"allow\" decisions (instead of `{ behavior: \"allow\" }`)\n3. Returns `{ behavior: \"deny\", message }` for \"deny\" decisions (unchanged)\n\n**What was not tested**: End-to-end verification with a live Claude Code 2.1.x session was not performed — it would require the full Claude Code CLI setup. The fix is validated at the permission-response rendering level, which is the exact layer where the schema mismatch occurred.\n\n## Tests and validation\n\n| Test Type | Result | Details |\n|-----------|--------|---------|\n| Unit Tests | ✅ | 75/75 passed |\n\n## Risk checklist\n\nDid user-visible behavior change? (`Yes` / `No`)\n\n**Yes** — users of Claude Code >= 2.1.x will no longer see `ZodError` when approving tool calls. Users of Claude Code < 2.1.x are unaffected (the `updatedInput` field is accepted by both old and new schemas). Deny behavior is unchanged.\n\nDid config, environment, or migration behavior change? (`Yes` / `No`)\n\n**No**\n\nDid security, auth, secrets, network, or tool execution behavior change? (`Yes` / `No`)\n\n**No**\n\n## Current review state\n\nWhat is the next action?\n- Maintainer review\n",
